<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Any student who took an Advanced Placement course in high school and has earned a grade of three or above on the final standardized AP Exam will be awarded college credits by the Josephinum for any course other than English Composition. In order to be awarded credit in English Composition, a student must earn a grade of four or above.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.pcj.edu/registrar/2011-12catalog.pdf" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

